I need to identify the net profit (the amount retained after all expenses) and extract 5 component sub-items that contribute to this calculation from the income statement.

Looking at the income statement:
- Net Profit is explicitly listed as 1103190.60
- This is calculated as Profit Before Tax (1393861.65) minus Tax Expense (290671.05)

For the 5 component sub-items, I'll select the key items that flow into this final profit calculation:
1. Total Revenue: 5813420.67
2. Total Cost: 3175000.00 
3. Total Expenses: 1255269.09
4. Interest Income: 10710.07
5. Tax Expense: 290671.05

The calculation flow is:
- Total Revenue (5813420.67) - Total Cost (3175000.00) = Gross Profit (2638420.67)
- Gross Profit (2638420.67) - Total Expenses (1255269.09) + Interest Income (10710.07) = Profit Before Tax (1393861.65)
- Profit Before Tax (1393861.65) - Tax Expense (290671.05) = Net Profit (1103190.60)
